org.osate.xtext.aadl2.agcl.analysis.verifiers

Interface ModelChecker

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    NuSMVModelChecker
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ModelCheckerImpl, NuSMVModelCheckerImpl

    public interface ModelChecker
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    The interface of model checkers.

    This interface is intended to be used in two possible ways:

    1. verify a single VerificationUnit and return a VerificationResult
    2. verifiy of a collection of VerificationUnits and collect all results in a ResultsCollection.
    Typical use: 

     Resource r = ...;
 Model m1 = ...;
 Specification s1 = ...;
 Viewpoint v1 = ...;
 Component c1 = ...;
 VerificationUnit vc1 = VerifiersFactory.eINSTANCE.createVerificationUnit();
 vc1.setModel(m1);
 vc1.setSpecification(s1);
 vc1.setViewpoint(v1);
 vc1.setComponetn(c1);
 // possibly more VerificationUnits
 ModelChecker mc = SomeModelCheckerFactory.eINSTANCE.createSomeModelChecker(); // A concrete subclass of ModelCheckerImpl
 mc.setUp(r);
 // use case 1
 VerificationResult result = mc.checkVerificationUnit(vc);
 // ... or 
 // use case 2
 mc.addVerificationUnit(vc1);
 mc.addVerificationUnit(vc2);
 // ...
 mv.checkAll();
 ResultsCollection rc = mc.getResultsCollection();

    The setUp(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.resource.Resource) method records the Resource context and creates a ResultsCollection to record all results when invoked with checkAll().

    The following features are supported:

    • Resource Context
    • Results
    • Verification Units
    • Viewpoint Collection
    • Component Collection

    See Also:
    VerifiersPackage.getModelChecker()

      • callExternal

        ModelCheckerOutput callExternal(ModelCheckerInput input)
        Invokes an external model-checker by performing a system call.

        This method must be implemented by subclasses.

        Parameters:
        input - an object encapsulating the input expected by the model-checker (e.g., containing references to input files provided to the model-checker)
        Returns:
        an object encapsulating the results produced by the model-checker (e.g., containing references to files produced by the model-checker)
